cs.SE, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.PL, cs.DC 

The paper discusses the use of search-based techniques in software engineering, specifically for self-adaptive systems. This falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as search-based techniques involve optimization algorithms. Self-adaptive systems also fall under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also discusses programming languages (cs.PL) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) in the context of self-adaptive systems.
